        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 20 at 9:36AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 935 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 25 miles west of Choteau to
12 miles west of Augusta. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Augusta, Nilan Reservoir, Pishkun Reservoir, and Bynum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
